    <sect2 id="s2refproptoolbar">
      <title>Property Toolbars</title>

      <para>Whilst all property sheets differ, many have toolbars. To avoid
        repetition, the toobar buttons are all gathered in this
        section.</para>

      <para>The property toolbar buttons can be grouped into three
        sets.</para>

      <!-- Note that there are three groupings of buttons -->
        
      <orderedlist>
        <listitem><para>Those that appear on most property sheets (Up,
          Back, Forward and Delete).</para></listitem>

        <listitem><para>Those that appear only on package property
          sheets, including Model property sheets (Add Class, Add
          Interface, Add Datatype, Add Stereotype, Add Actor, Add Use
          Case, Add Subpackage, Add Generalization and Add
          Realization). There is one exception, in that the Add Use Case
          button appears on the Use Case property sheet. However it does
          nothing, and this is presumably a mistake.</para></listitem>

        <listitem><para>Those that appear only Class and Interface
          property sheets (Add Attributed, Add Operations and Add Inner
          Class).</para></listitem>
      </orderedlist>

